data.Name: Jesika Von Rabbit
data.Bio: Dubbed “California's ultimate postmodern, intergalactic pop provocateur “ by the LA Weekly, Jesika von Rabbit formed the group Gram Rabbit with partner Todd Rutherford sparking a creative force unlike any other at the time. Their debut album "Music to Start a Cult To" was released to rave reviews and the LA Weekly hailed them as LA's Best New Artist.
